import cv2
import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt

img = cv2.imread('gatitos.jpg')
cv2.imshow('gatitos.jpg', img)

color = ('b','g','r')

for i, c in enumerate(color):
    hist = cv2.calcHist([img], [i], None, [256], [0, 256])
    cv2.normalize(hist,hist,alpha=0,beta=1,norm_type=cv2.NORM_MINMAX)
    plt.plot(hist, color = c)
    plt.xlim([0,256])

plt.show()

cv2.destroyAllWindows()

img = cv2.imread('gatitos.jpg', cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
cv2.imshow('gatitos.jpg', img)

hist = cv2.calcHist([img], [0], None, [256], [0, 256])

cv2.normalize(hist,hist,alpha=0,beta=1,norm_type=cv2.NORM_MINMAX)

plt.plot(hist, color='gray' )

plt.xlabel('intensidad de iluminacion')
plt.ylabel('cantidad de pixeles')
plt.show()

cv2.destroyAllWindows()

img0 = cv2.imread('monos_bri.jpg')
img1 = cv2.imread('monos_ori.jpg')
img2 = cv2.imread('monos_os.jpg')

imas = [img0,img1,img2]
color = ('c','m','y')

#c = aguamarina/ cian
#m = magenta
#y = amarillo

for i, c in enumerate(color):
    hist = cv2.calcHist([imas[i]], [i], None, [256], [0, 256])
    cv2.normalize(hist,hist,alpha=0,beta=1,norm_type=cv2.NORM_MINMAX)
    plt.plot(hist, color = c)
    plt.xlim([0,256])

plt.show()

img0=cv2.cvtColor(img0,cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
img1=cv2.cvtColor(img1,cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
img2=cv2.cvtColor(img2,cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)

plt.figure();
plt.subplot(1,3,1),plt.imshow(img0),plt.xticks([]), plt.yticks([]),plt.title('Luminiza')
plt.subplot(1,3,2),plt.imshow(img1),plt.xticks([]), plt.yticks([]),plt.title('Normal')
plt.subplot(1,3,3),plt.imshow(img2),plt.xticks([]), plt.yticks([]),plt.title('Oscura')   
plt.subplots_adjust(top=4, bottom=0.1, left=0.10, right=3, hspace=0.1, wspace=0.2)
